text: Tyrrell County is a county located in the U.S. state of North Carolina. As of the 2020 census, the population was 3,245 making it the least populous county in the state. Its county seat is Columbia. The county was created in 1729 as Tyrrell Precinct and gained county status in 1739. == References == Category:1730s establishments in North Carolina Category:1739 establishments Category:North Carolina counties
